newsitem.title: UK: Kingfisher share succumbs to profit-taking.
newsitem.headline: Kingfisher share succumbs to profit-taking.

text.p: Shares in UK retail group Kingfisher Plc slid in an otherwise firm market on Tuesday as investors booked profits, marketmakers said.
Kingfisher shares, which have gained over 23 percent since the start of the year, were down 9-1/2p at 670-1/2p at 0838 GMT.
Most other retailers were firm in quiet dealings.

"The shares have had a good run this year. I think we're seeing profit-taking ahead of the interim figures tomorrow. But it's pretty low-level and we don't see any major problems with the stock," said one dealer.
